title: For Sale:  Original 1849 Highly Engraved Cased Colt w/all original tools/case/flask, 5 1/2 bbl
postcontent:
Extensively engraved 1849 Colt by Gustav Young with rare second wolf's head - one on frame near rammer, one on the hammer itself.  Matching serial numbers throughout.  

Beautiful walnut grips (original), brass trigger guard, original Colt wooden case is in very good condition and all wood grain matches with minor fading in the (original) silk on the lid interior, no rust on weapon or accoutrements.  Wonderful patina, no pitting, crisp engraving.  A great example of one of the iconic firearms of the early American West.

It is, as typical of this weapon, a .36 caliber 5-shot cap-and-ball revolver - the bore is good, chambers of cylinder are good, percussion nipples also in nice condition.  Cocking spur requires adjustment as hammer does not stay cocked.

Serious inquiries only...will supply photos for serious buyers.  Sorry, not interested in trades at this particular time...thanks though.

FTF only, cash only.

title: For Sale:  WTS/WTT Saiga 12 Modified and Converted
postcontent:
If you are not familiar with the Saiga 12, it is a 12GA AK that is produced in the same factory as the original AK 47 in Russia. It comes with one 5 & one 10 round magazine.

This is not the $600.00 Sporter version you buy from the dealers.

Here is what has been done to convert from the Sporter version to the AK combat version.

1. Original trigger group removed
2. Move trigger guard forward 2 inches.
3. Install new US polished Tapco trigger forward 2 inches.
4. Install Saw style pistol grip in place of old trigger group.
5. Remove old Sporter style stock and replace with T1 (AR) style collapsible stock.
6. Press off gas block and increase gas port sizes to improve function of inexpensive ammo.
7. Reshape barrel feed to improve shell feeding.
8. Polish bolt to improve functionality.
9. The safety has been modified to function as a bolt hold open.

I have built and own several of these. They are not your standard Saiga all parts that are replaced re-classify it as a US firearm.
Looking for a PTR 91 G3. Trades (partial or otherwise)considered: other fire arms, ammo, reloading equipment.

REDACTED
REDACTED

title: For Sale/Trade:  38 S&W special ctg
postcontent:
38 Military & Police/1905 Hand Ejector, 4th Change. They were made between 1915 and 1942 within a serial number range running from about 241,704 to 999,999. This revolver was made around 1924.

  gun has a heat treated cylinder so it should be fine with modern standard velocity ammunition. Keep away from, or at least minimize use of Plus P ammo.  gun does incorporate a hammer block safety, but in WWII a similar gun was dropped, resulting in it firing when the hammer block failed. A new hammer block was designed and continues in use till today. It may be prudent if the gun is kept loaded to leave the hammer down on an empty chamber.

make an offer on pistol/rifle trade or cash.
